  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The objective of the CABERNET Trial is to evaluate the safety and efficacy of focal delivery
      of radiation for the treatment of subfoveal choroidal neovascularization (CNV) associated
      with wet age-related macular degeneration (AMD). The Epi-Rad90™ Ophthalmic System treats
      neovascularization of retinal tissue by means of a focal, directional delivery of radiation
      to the target tissues in the retina. Using standard vitreoretinal surgical techniques, the
      sealed radiation source is placed temporarily over the retinal lesion by means of a handheld
      medical device.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Therapeutic advances in the arena of neovascular age-related macular degeneration (AMD) have
      provided multiple treatment options for the disease. Radiotherapy has been studied in
      multiple clinical trials in the past with many studies showing a therapeutic benefit.
      Treatment with radiotherapy and anti-VEGF compounds is a promising approach to treating AMD.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
